{"author":{"id":"bf52274e4b8baa03d436abcc532c02b6a719b9a772a7e952e18fcc8627570e5f"},"ops":[{"type":1,"timestamp":1774485801,"nonce":"fasFUkABQfyOf1mUmYden4mGciA=","title":"Show key provenance in error messages","message":"When a step is supplied with an unknown key, the error message lists the known keys. But it doesn't show where those keys came from (which step produced them, or whether they're global inputs). Something like:\n```\nStep print supplied with unknown key #:msg. Known keys at this step are:\n#:message (from workflow input)\n#:sorted (from step sort-words)\n```\nwould be nice. We already carry provenance info on `\u003ckey\u003e` objects—so this is mostly a presentation change.","files":null}]}